channel.title: Papers with Code: Latest (unofficial)
channel.description: As a disclaimer, this is an unofficial feed and has no affiliation with Papers with Code.

item.title: 1st Place Solution to MultiEarth 2023 Challenge on Multimodal SAR-to-EO Image Translation
item.description: The Multimodal Learning for Earth and Environment Workshop (MultiEarth 2023) aims to harness the substantial amount of remote sensing data gathered over extensive periods for the monitoring and analysis of Earth's ecosystems'health.

item.title: SoftGPT: Learn Goal-oriented Soft Object Manipulation Skills by Generative Pre-trained Heterogeneous Graph Transformer
item.description: Soft object manipulation tasks in domestic scenes pose a significant challenge for existing robotic skill learning techniques due to their complex dynamics and variable shape characteristics.

item.title: Curriculum Knowledge Switching for Pancreas Segmentation
item.description: Pancreas segmentation is challenging due to the small proportion and highly changeable anatomical structure.

item.title: Squeeze, Recover and Relabel: Dataset Condensation at ImageNet Scale From A New Perspective
item.description: We present a new dataset condensation framework termed Squeeze, Recover and Relabel (SRe$^2$L) that decouples the bilevel optimization of model and synthetic data during training, to handle varying scales of datasets, model architectures and image resolutions for effective dataset condensation.

item.title: PyKoopman: A Python Package for Data-Driven Approximation of the Koopman Operator
item.description: PyKoopman is a Python package for the data-driven approximation of the Koopman operator associated with a dynamical system.

item.title: MFCCGAN: A Novel MFCC-Based Speech Synthesizer Using Adversarial Learning
item.description: We evaluated the model based on a popular intrusive objective speech intelligibility measure (STOI) and quality (NISQA score).

item.title: Evading Forensic Classifiers with Attribute-Conditioned Adversarial Faces
item.description: While these forensic models can detect whether a face image is synthetic or real with high accuracy, they are also vulnerable to adversarial attacks.

item.title: Fitted Value Iteration Methods for Bicausal Optimal Transport
item.description: We develop a fitted value iteration (FVI) method to compute bicausal optimal transport (OT) where couplings have an adapted structure.

item.title: xSIM++: An Improved Proxy to Bitext Mining Performance for Low-Resource Languages
item.description: In comparison to xSIM, we show that xSIM++ is better correlated with the downstream BLEU scores of translation systems trained on mined bitexts, providing a reliable proxy of bitext mining performance without needing to run expensive bitext mining pipelines.

item.title: A Hierarchical Approach to exploiting Multiple Datasets from TalkBank
item.description: TalkBank is an online database that facilitates the sharing of linguistics research data.

item.title: Lumbar spine segmentation in MR images: a dataset and a public benchmark
item.description: This paper presents a large publicly available multi-center lumbar spine magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) dataset with reference segmentations of vertebrae, intervertebral discs (IVDs), and spinal canal.

item.title: Efficient ResNets: Residual Network Design
item.description: We show that our ResNet achieves a test accuracy of 96. 04% on CIFAR-10 which is much higher than ResNet18 (which has greater than 11 million trainable parameters) when equipped with a number of training strategies and suitable ResNet hyperparameters.

item.title: Benchmarking and Analyzing 3D-aware Image Synthesis with a Modularized Codebase
item.description: Despite the rapid advance of 3D-aware image synthesis, existing studies usually adopt a mixture of techniques and tricks, leaving it unclear how each part contributes to the final performance in terms of generality.

item.title: Joint Dense-Point Representation for Contour-Aware Graph Segmentation
item.description: We present a novel methodology that combines graph and dense segmentation techniques by jointly learning both point and pixel contour representations, thereby leveraging the benefits of each approach.

item.title: Polygon Detection for Room Layout Estimation using Heterogeneous Graphs and Wireframes
item.description: This paper presents a neural network based semantic plane detection method utilizing polygon representations.

item.title: StarVQA+: Co-training Space-Time Attention for Video Quality Assessment

item.title: Quantifying Node-based Core Resilience
item.description: We first show that a previously proposed measure, Core Strength, does not correctly capture the core resilience of a node upon edge removals.

item.title: RSMT: Real-time Stylized Motion Transition for Characters

item.description: For example, the pair of 'A' and 'V' shows a high ambigramability (that is, it is easy to generate their ambigrams), and the pair of 'D' and 'K' shows a lower ambigramability.

item.title: Accelerating Multiframe Blind Deconvolution via Deep Learning
item.description: In this method, the image restoration problem is solved with a gradient descent method that is unrolled and accelerated aided by a few small neural networks.

item.title: M-VAAL: Multimodal Variational Adversarial Active Learning for Downstream Medical Image Analysis Tasks

item.title: Dynamic Implicit Image Function for Efficient Arbitrary-Scale Image Representation

item.title: VisoGender: A dataset for benchmarking gender bias in image-text pronoun resolution

item.title: Sample Attackability in Natural Language Adversarial Attacks

item.title: NeuroCLIP: Neuromorphic Data Understanding by CLIP and SNN

item.title: Benchmark data to study the influence of pre-training on explanation performance in MR image classification
item.description: Here, we propose a benchmark dataset that allows for quantifying explanation performance in a realistic magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) classification task.

item.title: AdCraft: An Advanced Reinforcement Learning Benchmark Environment for Search Engine Marketing Optimization

item.title: EquiformerV2: Improved Equivariant Transformer for Scaling to Higher-Degree Representations

item.title: Fast Segment Anything

item.title: GADBench: Revisiting and Benchmarking Supervised Graph Anomaly Detection
item.description: With a long history of traditional Graph Anomaly Detection (GAD) algorithms and recently popular Graph Neural Networks (GNNs), it is still not clear (1) how they perform under a standard comprehensive setting, (2) whether GNNs outperform traditional algorithms such as tree ensembles, and (3) their efficiency on large-scale graphs.

item.title: Polytope: An Algorithm for Efficient Feature Extraction on Hypercubes
